Let $\theta = \angle AOP.$  Then $\angle BOP = 180^\circ - \theta,$ so
\begin{align*}
\cos \theta &= \frac{OP}{OA} = \frac{\sqrt{r^2 + h^2}}{125}, \\
\cos (180^\circ - \theta) &= \frac{OP}{OB} = \frac{\sqrt{r^2 + h^2}}{375 \sqrt{2}}.
