Then $BO = x,$ so $AO = \sqrt{1 - x^2}.$  Since $BO \perp AO,$
\[a^2 = x^2 + (1 - x^2) = 1.\]Also, $CO = x - b,$ so
\[b^2 = (x - b)^2 + (1 - x^2) = 2bx - x^2 + 1.\]Furthermore, $CO = OD,$ so
\[b = \sqrt{1 - x^2} - x.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
2bx - x^2 + 1 &= (2x - 2x \sqrt{1 - x^2}) x - x^2 + 1 \\
&= 2x^2 \sqrt{1 - x^2} + 1 - x^2.
